<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EMU Will Start on Time: Santer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 21 (Xinhua) -- A single European currency
will start on time with or without Britain, the European
Commission President Jacques Santer said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on Britain's Sky Television, Santer said that he is
quite confident the convergence criteria of Maastricht will be
reached on time and the European Economic and Monetary Union (EMU)
will start operation on time on January 1, 1999.
</P>
<P>
+We now have real convergence of our economic policies, we have
now very low interest rates, so at this moment there is real
stability,+ he said.
</P>
<P>
Santer, who had just visited Scotland last week, said that
British membership in EMU would be welcomed, as the EU wants
Britain to be at its heart.
</P>
<P>
UK Foreign Secretary Robin Cook said last Friday that the UK
was unlikely to join EMU in 1999, but would find it hard to stay
out if it proved successful.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
