<HEADLINE> Foreign Parties Congratulate on Jiang's Re-election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Following is a partial list
of political parties and leaders from around the world who have
sent congratulations to Jiang Zemin on his re-election as general
secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC):
</P>
<P>
Antonio Mascarenhas Monteiro, president of Cape Verde;
</P>
<P>
Carlos Veiga, prime minister of Cape Verde and chairman of its
ruling party Movement for Democracy;
</P>
<P>
Charles Mukasi, president of the Burundian Party of Union for
National Progress (UPRONA);
</P>
<P>
Alamin Mohammed, secretary general of the People's Front for
Democracy and Justice (PFDJ) of Eritrea;
</P>
<P>
J. J. Kamotho, secretary general of Kenya African National
Union (KANU);
</P>
<P>
Petre Roman, president, and Adrian Severin, vice president of
the Democratic Party of Romania;
</P>
<P>
Lopo do Nascimento, secretary general of the People's Movement
of the Liberation of Angola (PMLA). 
