<HEADLINE> Greece, Albania to Sign New Cooperation Protocol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Greece and Albania will sign a
new cooperation protocol as part of efforts to strengthen the
cooperation between their armed forces, the semi-official Athens
News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The protocol will be signed by Greek Defense Minister Akis
Tsohatzopoulos and his Albanian counterpart Sabit Brokaj who
starts a three-day visit to Greece next Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The new accord based on a bilateral cooperation agreement
reached in early August, will finalize the specific areas of
cooperation between a Greek army company and the Albanian armed
forces for re-organization of the army. 
</P>
</TEXT>
