<HEADLINE> Dar Police Detain 59 Suspects of Illegal Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Police in Dar es
Salaam have detained 59 people for allegedly being in possession
of different items including drugs and illicit brew (gongo).
</P>
<P>
The suspects were arrested in different parts of the city
during a police swoop over the weekend, Regional Police Commander
Alfred gewe told the press here today.
</P>
<P>
During the operation, 88.5 liters of gongo, 51 rolls of bhang
(a kind of Indian marijuana), 65.5 pellets of bhang and 5 pellets
of cocaine were impounded.
</P>
<P>
Police in the Tanzanian capital in recent months have
intensified the fight against the possession of illicit brew and
narcotics which are harmful to people's health. 
</P>
</TEXT>
