<HEADLINE> 4 Hospital Employees Detained in Investigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Four staff members of Al Khanka
Hospital here were detained today for investigations of the escape
from the hospital of a man who carried out a fatal attack on a
tourist bus here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Attorney General of the Higher State Security
Prosecution Hisham Saraya issued the order today that Nessim Abdel
Malak Nessim, director for psychological and nerve diseases and
Sayed Ahmed Al Qot, director of psychological health, and two male
nursing attendants be taken into custody for 15 days.
</P>
<P>
The four people were charged with accepting cash bribes from
the attacker and aiding his escape from the hospital, Egypt's
Middle East News Agency (MENA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Saber Mohamed Farahat reportedly escaped from the hospital
three days before launching his attack, killing nine German
tourists and the Egyptian driver and wounding at least 24 people,
including seven Germans.
</P>
<P>
Farahat was one of the two suspects detained at the scene of
the attack.
</P>
<P>
MENA said the Prosecution will question Farahat's mother about
the circumstances surrounding his life, his behavior towards his
family members and neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak issued an order to
transfer the supervision of the five Hospitals of Khanka,
Abbassia, Heliopolis, Helwan and Alexandria for Psychological and
mental diseases from local administrations to the Ministry of
Health in an effort to ensure management discipline. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
