<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oman, Britain Sign Military Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Oman and Britain today
signed a military agreement to upgrade fighters for Omani
Air force, the Omani news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed in the Omani capital of Muscat by
Badr bin Saud bin Harib al Busaede, Oman's minister in charge of
defense affairs, and British Secretary of State for Defense
George Robertson who arrived in Muscat today for a two-day
visit, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Britain will help Oman refit its
warplanes to make them have the similar capabilities of
"Jacwar-97", a Britain-made fighter which is equipped with
sophisticated weapons and electronic installations, it said.
</P>
<P>
The agency gave no further details about the agreement, but
informed sources said the warplane project will cost billions of
U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
