<HEADLINE> PLA Officers Discuss CPC Congress Policies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Three departments of the
People's Liberation Army -- the General Staff HQ, the General
Political Department, and the General Logistics Department --
today gave full support to the policies and resolutions of the
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) that
ended on Friday.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of high-ranking officers, Fu Quanyou, chief of PLA
General Staff and a member of the Central Military Commission,
said that the armed forces should stick to the spirit of the CPC
National Congress, and to Deng Xiaoping's theory in building the
military.
</P>
<P>
PLA officers and men should be loyal to the CPC leadership and
be steadfast in obeying the CPC Central Committee and the Central
Military Commission, which is headed by General Secretary Jiang
Zemin, Fu said.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the armed forced to support the central
government's policy giving economic development top priority and
to improve the military's combat strength.
</P>
<P>
Yu Yongbo, director of the General Political Department, said
at a conference discussing the Congress's policies that the
Chinese armed forces should be armed with Deng Xiaoping's theory
and should be loyal to the the CPC leadership, with Jiang Zemin at
the core. He asked them to study CPC policies and to work for
military unity.
</P>
<P>
Wang Ke, director of the General Logistics Department, said
that personnel working in the logistics institutions should adhere
to Central Military Commission Chairman Jiang Zemin's instructions
and to step up reforms in PLA logistics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
