<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets IMF Managing Director (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
met today with Michel Camdessus, Managing Director of the
International Monetary Fund (IMF), who is here for the annual
meetings of the World Bank Group and the IMF.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng expressed welcome to and congratulations for the annual
 meetings of the two international financial institutions to be
held in Hong Kong and wished the meetings a complete success.
</P>
<P>
In the past 20 years and more, he said, the IMF has kept good
ties with China and both sides have made remarkable progress in
cooperation in fund loan, policy dialogue and technical
assistance.
</P>
<P>
The IMF has shown great concern about China's economic
development, putting forth some positive policy proposals and
playing an advisory role, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng indicated that the IMF's rating of China's economic
development has helped the international community understand
China better.
</P>
<P>
With the gradual establishment of the structure of China's
socialist market economy and further integration of China's
economy into the global economy, he said, greater cooperation and
exchanges between China and the IMF will be seen and China's role
in the IMF will be enhanced.
</P>
</TEXT>
