<HEADLINE> Clinton Visits U.N. Headquarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill
Clinton arrived in the United Nations in New York Monday morning
to address the 52nd session of the U.N. General Assembly and
confer with U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
Clinton and his party were met at the entrance of the
U.N. building by Annan before going to Annan's office.
</P>
<P>
Washington has repeatedly voiced backing to the U.N. reform
package put forward in mid-July by the U.N. secretary-general.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Permanent Representative here Bill Richadson said before
the opening of the 52nd session that he expected the session to
focus on the reform package that calls for reduced personnel of
the world body and annual budget while creating a new post of
deputy secretary-general to assume administrative duties.
</P>
<P>
Clinton is also expected to pay a courtesy call to the new
President of U.N. General Assembly, Hennadiy Udovenko, who was
elected last week at the opening meeting of the session. 
</P>
