<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets IMF Managing Director (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Camdessus said that facts have proved the cooperation between
the IMF and China has been successful and has laid a solid
foundation for future cooperation. The IMF is fully confident in
further developing its ties with China.
</P>
<P>
He also said that, through the IMF, China has given a lot of
help to the world's poorest countries, which has won wide
acclaim. The IMF highly appreciates the efforts made by China in
this respect and expects to expand cooperation with China in the
future.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng briefed Camdessus on the economic strategies and
policies decided on at the just-concluded 15th National Congress
of the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Camdessus said that the decisions made at the Congress are both
 wise and timely, providing sound prospects for the cooperation
between the IMF and China.
</P>
<P>
He said that the IMF is very happy to hold the annual meetings
jointly with the World Bank Group in Hong Kong after its return to
 China. Participants of the meetings have seen for themselves that
 the policy of "one country, two systems" is feasible in Hong Kong
 and Hong Kong is full of hope.
</P>
<P>
Also present at the meeting were Deputy Secretary-General of
the State Council He Chunlin, Governor of the People's Bank of
China Dai Xianglong, and Director of the Foreign Affairs Office of
 the State Council Liu Huaqiu.  
</P>
