<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Office for Taiwan Affairs
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
the Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council today expressed
full support to the 15th CPC Congress resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yunlin, director of the two offices, called for China's
early reunification in keeping with Jiang Zemin's instructions at
the Congress to implement the "peaceful reunification and one
country, two systems" policy.
</P>
<P>
He said that the policies on Taiwan put forward by the CPC 15th
National Congress should be implemented to the letter.
</P>
<P>
Other officials said that the Congress will have a significant
impact on China's development in the 21st century and will
increase exchanges across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
They said that in his political report to the congress, Jiang
Zemin appealed for negotiations on ending hostilities across the
Taiwan Straits, in accordance with the "one China" principle.
</P>
<P>
They said that Taiwan authorities should respond to the CPC
proposals as soon as possible and that the CPC welcomes the advice
and suggestions of all the Taiwan people, except for a handful of
notorious splittists.
</P>
<P>
The noted that CPC's proposal will serve the immediate
interests of the Taiwan compatriots and the fundamental interests
of the Chinese nation. So, it will be supported by Taiwan
compatriots. 
