<HEADLINE> Nepali Government Reshuffled Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Prime Minister
Lokendra Bahadur Chand Monday effected some changes in his cabinet
again while the main opposition party, the Nepali Congress, is
planning to lodge a no-confidence motion against the present
coalition government.
</P>
<P>
With the resignations of the minister for law and justice and
ministers of state for health and for local development accepted
by King Birendra, Prime Minister Chand gave the post of minister
for law and justice to Minister for Works and Transport Bharat
Mohan Adhikari.
</P>
<P>
He also transferred Gajendra Narayan Singh from the post of
minister for supplies to that of minister without portfolio and
made Moti Prasad Pahadi minister for supplies, Palten Gurung
minister of state for supplies and Naresh Bahadur Singh minister
of state for forests and soil conservation, the official RSS news
agency said.
</P>
<P>
The three new faces -- Palten Gurung, Moti Pahadi and Naresh
Bahadur Singh -- are all independents.
</P>
<P>
This is the sixth time that Chand has reshuffled his cabinet
since taking office in March.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a spokesman of the Parliament Secretariat confirmed
that the Nepali Congress has registered a no-confidence motion
against the government in the secretariat.  
</P>
</TEXT>
