<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 54.13 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 22 (Xinhua)-- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market today lost 54.13 points to 3770
as against last week's close of 3825.12.
</P>
<P>
The national index also dipped by 22.33 points to 1641.72 from
the previous close of 1664.05.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were quoted lower at
369.41 and 169.25 compared with last weekend's closes of 373.44
and 170.81 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Share prices continued their down-drift even on the opening day
of the new account on the BSE market today on fresh bull
liquidation and selling by foreign institutional investors.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that when the main operators turned sellers, it
was difficult for the market to sustain at the higher level at a
time when foreign funds had kept away.  
</P>
</TEXT>
