<HEADLINE> EU Approves Humanitarian Aid to Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission,
executive body of the European Union, today approved 7.25 ECU (8
million U.S. dollars) worth of humanitarian aid for Palestinians
living on the West Bank, the Gaza Strip and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The aid will enable the partner organizations of the European
Community Humanitarian Office to provide mainly medical aid to
these people over the next six months.
</P>
<P>
On the West Bank and the Gaza Strip, most of the funding will
be spent on assisting public and private hospitals, while the
funding in Lebanon will be used for medical aid and for covering
hospitalization costs for United Nations Relief and Works Agency
beneficiaries.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission has granted earlier this year a special
medical aid worth 350,000 ECU for the Lebanese in Lebanon. Last
year, the European Community Humanitarian Office spent 13.4
million ECU in Palestine and Lebanon. 
</P>
