<HEADLINE> Ramos Calls for National Unity to Face Tasks Ahead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos here today called on the Filipinos to follow the
government's lead in facing the challenges of poverty and economic
development to move the country to the next millennium.
</P>
<P>
Renewing his call for national unity, Ramos said the country
could become a more powerful economy by the 21st century "if we do
not compromise national gains we have already won together and not
allow them to be eroded by politically inspired divisiveness and
factionalism."
</P>
<P>
After Sunday's peaceful mass rally against charter changes
seeking to extend his term, Ramos has called on the people to heal
the wounds and bind the nation together to "go back to work and
move on."
</P>
<P>
In the past few months, charter change moves have caused
political divisiveness and uncertainties in the country, prompting
about half a million people to attend Sunday's rally in Manila.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said the government must now focus on fighting poverty
and sustaining economic development by raising productivity and
attracting more investments through various programs.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, he has urged the Philippine Congress to set aside the
debates regarding constitutional amendments and work for the
passage of laws urgently needed to make the country and the
Filipinos more competitive.  
</P>
</TEXT>
