<HEADLINE> Nigeria's Inflation Rate Down to 15.7 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's inflation rate slid
down to 15.7 percent in July, according to latest figures from
the Federal Offices of Statistics (FOS).
</P>
<P>
The figure is 1.8 percent down from June and 0.07 percent
above the goal of 15 percent projected by the government for the
whole year of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, the rate of inflation has
remained moderate, recording a downward movement from 28 percent
at the end of 1996 to the present level.
</P>
<P>
The government's objective is to bring down the inflation rate
to one digit by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The FOS noted, however, there is yet no corresponding
decreases in the prices of goods and services.
</P>
<P>
From June to July, 1997, the composite consumer price index
rose from 2929.0 to 3012.3, up by 2.8 percent. 
</P>
