<HEADLINE> Explanation on Amendments to CPC Constitution (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- A leading official with the
Secretariat of the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) recently explained in an interview with Xinhua the
Amendments to the Party Constitution approved by the 15th National
Party Congress, which closed on September 18.
</P>
<P>
The official said the revisions mainly focused on more clearly
defining Deng Xiaoping Theory as the guiding ideology of the Party.
</P>
<P>
At the Seventh National Congress of the Party, Mao Zedong
Thought, the integration of the theories of Marxism-Leninism with
the practice of the Chinese revolution, was named the prominent
ideology of the Communist Party of China. Doing this was of the
utmost importance for the success of the Chinese revolution and
construction, he said.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of the Third Plenary Session of the 11th Party
Central Committee, the 12th, 13th and especially the 14th National
Congresses of the Party, the 15th congress has established Deng
Xiaoping Theory, a continuation of Mao Zedong Thought, as the
Party's guiding ideology.
</P>
<P>
This decision, made at a national Party congress after the
theory had been tested for nearly two decades during the reform
and opening up and following the death of Comrade Deng Xiaoping,
is bound to play an extremely important role in the successful
development of the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The 15th National Congress pledges to hold high the great
banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory for an all-round advancement of the
cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics into the
21st century.
</P>
<P>
Marxism-Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory
constitute a unified scientific system. In present-day China,
adhering to Deng Xiaoping Theory means genuinely adhering to
Marxism-Leninism and Mao Zedong Thought, and Holding high the
banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory means holding high the banner of
Marxism-Leninism and Mao Zedong Thought, the official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970922.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Explanation on Amendments to CPC Constitution (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to a question on the revision on the General
Program of the Constitution of the CPC, the official said the
amended constitution stipulates: "The Communist Party of China
takes Marxism-Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought and Deng Xiaoping
Theory as its guide to action."
</P>
<P>
Following the original expositions of Marxism-Leninism and Mao
Zedong Thought, the General Program of the amended Party
Constitution made some readjustments and additions to the theory
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, thus forming
the exposition of Deng Xiaoping Theory:
</P>
<P>
"Since the Third Plenum of the 11th Party Congress, the
communists, with Comrade Deng Xiaoping as their chief
representative, have reviewed the experience gained through their
successes and failures since the founding of the People's
Republic, liberated their minds, sought truth from facts, shifted
the focus of the work of the whole Party to economic development,
introduced reform and opened China to the outside world, thus
ushering in a new period of development of the socialist cause.
</P>
<P>
"They have gradually formulated the line, principles and
policies for building socialism with Chinese characteristics,
clarified the fundamental issues concerning how to build,
consolidate and develop socialism in China and created Deng
Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
"This theory is a product of the integration of the fundamental
tenets of Marxism-Leninism with the practice in present-day China
and the features of the times and is a continuation and
development of Mao Zedong Thought under the new historical
conditions.
</P>
<P>
"It represents a new stage of development of Marxism in
China. It is a Marxist theory for present-day China and a
crystallization of the collective wisdom of the Communist Party of
China and is guiding China's socialist modernization drive
forward."
</P>
<P>
The official also said that since the revised Party
constitution has stipulated in the General Program that "the
Communist Party of China takes Marxism-Leninism, Mao Zedong
Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory as its guide to action,"
amendments were made accordingly to Clause 1 of Article 3, Clause
2 of Article 31 and Clause 1 of Article 34, stipulating that the
Party members and the leading Party officials should
conscientiously study Marxism-Leninism, Mao Zedong Thought and
Deng Xiaoping Theory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
