<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Confident About HK Dollar Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu
Rongji today voiced his confidence in the stability of the Hong
Kong dollar despite the recent currency turmoil in Southeast Asian
countries.
</P>
<P>
Answering questions after his speech at a World Bank seminar on
China's economy here this afternoon, Zhu said that the authorities
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HK SAR) are fully
capable of defending the HK dollar.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has a robust economic growth with relatively less
bubble factors and its foreign exchange reserves total 86 billion
U.S. dollars, therefore its currency enjoys a stable position, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Although the HK dollar was affected to a limited extent by the
recent turmoil, "we haven't seen any big changes," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. dollar-pegged currency system has been working in Hong
Kong for over 13 years, and "I have learned from well-positioned
sources of the HK SAR government that they do not intend to change
such a system in the short or medium term," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
