<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Little Changed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar
finished little changed today, with the market bereft of any fresh
news to trade off.
</P>
<P>
The local unit closed at 71.93 US cents, compared to 71.90 US
cents previously.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the local unit had been sidelined today as market
attention focused on the U.S. dollar following the meeting of
Group of Seven finance ministers and central bank governors in
Hong Kong on the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The market were still digesting a communique released after the
gathering which was interpreted as indicating a preference for a
stronger yen.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar rose to 88.08 yen, from 87.58.
</P>
<P>
Looking ahead for the Australian dollar, market watchers said
further downside movement in the currency against the U.S. dollar
in the near term appeared limited.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was at 1.2773 marks, down from 1.2807.
