<HEADLINE> Poland's Solidarity Alliance Looks Set to Win Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Poland's triumphant Solidarity
alliance won a clear lead over the ruling Democratic Left Alliance
(SLD) in Sunday's elections, according to exit polls.
</P>
<P>
A poll by the public OBOP institute after voting stations
closed at 10.00 p.m. (2000 GMT), showed the Solidarity Election
Action (AWS) garnering 33.8 percent of the vote to 26.8 percent
for the SLD.
</P>
<P>
Ranking third was the Freedom Union, with 13.4 percent of the
votes, giving it a good chance of playing king-maker in future
coalition talks.
</P>
<P>
The only other parties looking set to pass the 5 percent
threshold were the co-ruling Peasant party, at 7 percent, and the
populist Movement for Reconstruction of Poland with 5.6 percent.
</P>
