<HEADLINE> 40 More Palestinians Arrested by Israeli forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Israeli security forces
have arrested more than 40 Hamas activists in the West bank villages
around Nablus area since Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli authorities have claimed that they were carrying
out the mass arrest after receiving information that Islamic
extremists had been planning to carry out an attack in Nablus,
local press said today.
</P>
<P>
This arrest operation is conducted as a part of the activities
to deter terror and smash Hamas' infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
For this campaign, the Israeli security mobilized the soldiers
of the Golani Brigade, undercover troops, paratroopers and border
policemen. They first clamped curfews and then raided the targets
they planned for.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli security forces Saturday night swept down a village
in the Nablus area. They asked the Palestinian local police to
remain in their station before carrying out their raid on several
Palestinian houses.
</P>
<P>
They surrounded the village, cut off telephone lines and
rounded up hundreds of villagers at a local girl school. 20 to 30
of the villagers were taken into custody by Israeli forces after
questioning.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 Palestinians have been arrested since the
suicide bomb attacks in Jerusalem on July 30 and September 4
that killed 25 people.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian National authority (PNA) and the Israeli
government have different explanations over the arrests. The
Israeli side said these Palestinians arrested are suspects
affiliated with Hamas or Islamic Jihad, two Islamic resistance
groups of Palestine. The PNA accused such arrests, saying they
were conducted within the PNA territories without solid
evidence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
