<HEADLINE> Chinese, Gabonese Defense Ministers Hold Talks in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The defense ministers of
China and Gabon held talks in Beijing today, agreeing that recent
years have witnessed successful cooperation between the two
countries in political, economic and cultural areas, and that
bilateral military contacts and cooperation have been satisfying
as well.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Minister of National Defense Chi Haotian, who is also
vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission and a state
councilor, told Gabonese Defense Minister Idriss Ngari that China
and Gabon share a tradition of friendship.
</P>
<P>
