<HEADLINE> British Defense Secretary Visits Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 22 (Xinhua) -- British Defense
Secretary George Robertson arrived here today on a three-day
official visit to boost British-Kuwaiti military relations.
</P>
<P>
This was the first visit by a British defense minister to the
sensitive Gulf region since Britain's Labor government took office
in May this year.
</P>
<P>
Robertson's visit here was part of his Gulf tour which already
took him to Oman and will take him to the United Arab
Emirates.
</P>
<P>
British diplomatic sources here said that during the visit
Robertson will meet Kuwaiti Emir Sheikh Jaber Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah,
his Kuwaiti counterpart Sheikh Salem Al-Sabah and Kuwaiti acting
Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Sheikh Salem Al-Sabah to
discuss defense matters.
</P>
<P>
He will also visit a British ship taking part in the mission of
enforcing international sanctions against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Britain's new Labor government reassured Kuwait right after it
assumed power in Mary that it would continue the policy undertaken
by the previous administration to ensure Kuwait's stability and
security.
</P>
<P>
The two countries reiterated their determination to strengthen
defense cooperation in all fields during Kuwaiti Defense Minister
Sheik Salem Sabah Al-Salem Al-Sabah's visit to London last
February.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Britain signed a defense cooperation agreement in
the wake of the 1991 Gulf War in which the U.S.-led allied forces
defeated Iraqi troops and drove them out of Kuwait. 
</P>
