<DOCNO> XIE19970922.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Inter-Bank Foreign Currency Trade Goes Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The inter-bank foreign currency
market in Vietnam has traded a total of 4.2 billion U.S. dollars
in the first eight months of this year, local reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The figure shows a remarkable increase of the money flowing
through the market, compared to 2.3 billion U.S. dollars in 1996
and 934 million dollars in 1995, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The inter-bank foreign currency market in the country, almost
trebling its size since its establishment in late 1994, consists
of 58 members including four state commercial banks, 28 joint
stock banks, 20 branches of foreign banks and two financial
companies.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's inter-bank foreign currency market has contributed to
balancing the domestic supply and demand for foreign currencies
and organizing and controlling foreign currency business as well
as preparing for setup of a foreign exchange market, the report
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
