<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Upbeat about China's Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu
Rongji here today told bankers and businessmen from all over the
world present at a World Bank seminar that he is positive that
China's present good economic situation will last.
</P>
<P>
Delivering a keynote speech at the seminar to envisage China's
economy in the 21st century, Zhu said that his confidence was
based on China's many favorable conditions, especially the correct
road that China has found which is suitable to the Chinese
conditions and will, step by step, lead China to modernization.
</P>
<P>
"This is what we call the road of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics" as pointed out by late Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping, he said.
</P>
<P>
The just-concluded 15th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) has laid out an all-round strategy for the
country's reform, opening-up and socialist modernization drive,
Zhu added.
</P>
<P>
He said that according to the plan, China's economy will grow
by eight percent per annum in the final years of this century and
the economy is expected to maintain a seven percent annual growth
rate for the first decade of the next century. This is very
similar to the forecast by the World Bank on China's development
up to 2020.
</P>
<P>
Great changes have taken place in China since the country
launched the reform and opening-up program in the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, China has reversed the once-overheating of the
economy and has brought inflation under control, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The price rise dropped to 1.4 percent in the first eight months
of this year and this year's economic growth rate is expected to
remain at around 10 percent. "We may say that China's economy has
not been so good for many years," he added.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, the annual increase of the grain output
reached over 20 million tons with another bumper harvest of summer
crops this year, Zhu said. Owing to climatic reasons, there may be
a fall in the autumn crop production, but the grain production of
the whole year will not be much lower than that of last year.
</P>
<P>
The adequate grain supply has helped stabilize the food prices
which account for a big portion of the daily consumption of the
Chinese people. This is an important reason for the rapid drop in
the price rise, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The foreign direct investment has amounted to over 100 billion
U.S. dollars in the three years between 1994 and 1996, about twice
that over a period of more than 10 years before 1994.
</P>
<P>
"There has also been a substantial increase in the foreign
exchange reserve from 18 billion U.S. dollars in 1993 to 131.6
billion now," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
"Some foreign friends are wondering whether this good economic
situation in China will last and whether there will be new
inflation," Zhu noted. "I am positive about the former. With the
experience gained in the past three years, we have already found
the methods to guard against and bring down inflation."
</P>
<P>
"So long as we continue to adopt these methods which prove to
be effective, this good economic situation will be consolidated
and last," he stressed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970922.0134 </DOCNO>
