<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji on Financial Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu
Rongji said here today that China has attached great importance to
and adopted positive measures in warding off financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
"Today's China enjoys abundance in its foreign exchange
reserve, stability of the currency value of the RMB and a stable
financial situation with sound development," Zhu told a World Bank
seminar on China's economic development prospects in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the necessity and usefulness for national and
international financial institutions to increase information
exchange and cooperation so as to "protect us from financial
risks".
</P>
<P>
Recently, he said, some of the Southeast Asian countries have
experienced financial volatility to varying degrees. "They are
taking measures to cope with the situation and the International
Monetary Fund is also vigorously organizing assistance."
</P>
<P>
"As far as I can see, the overall situation is taking a turn
for the better," he noted, saying that "given the rapid economic
development these countries have experienced in the past decade
and more and the industrial basis they have established, I'm fully
confident that they will be able to overcome the present
difficulty, successfully conduct economic restructuring, and
develop their economies steadily." 
</P>
</TEXT>
