<HEADLINE> Two Israeli Embassy Emissaries In Jordan Attacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Two Israeli embassy
emissaries in Amman, Jordan were attacked today by terrorists and
were lightly injured, Israeli Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Both the injured emissaries are receiving treatment in a
Jordanian hospital, the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Jordan policemen are hunting the attackers who opened fire from
a passing vehicle on the Israelis at about 07:30 local time
today. And the Jordanian authorities are cooperating with the
Israeli Embassy in Jordan in handling this matter, the Ministry
added.
</P>
<P>
This is the third terrorist attack on Israelis in Jordan in
the last six months. A Jordanian soldier opened fire and killed
seven Israeli schoolgirls on March 13 and was sentenced to life
imprisonment in July. A Israeli woman tourist was stabbed in
Jordan last April.
</P>
<P>
The assassination attempt came at a time when the Middle East
peace process have been deadlocked for months and the Palestinians
are protesting against Israeli Jews over their occupation of
houses in Ras al-Amud Arab neighborhood in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Jordan signed peace treaty with Israel in 1994 despite
opposition by many Jordanians, especially by those citizens who
are of Palestinian origin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
