<HEADLINE> Premier Li Reiterates Support to Hong Kong SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng today
assured Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa of the central government's
support to the government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
In a meeting here with Chief Executive Tung and other ranking
officials of the HK SAR at noon today, Li reiterated that the
policies of "one country, two systems" and "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong" with a high degree of autonomy will be
implemented after Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"The central government supports you and will not interfere in
your affairs," Li told Tung.
</P>
<P>
The HK SAR government is now operating well, Li noted, adding
that "you can do things on your own and you can rest assured."
</P>
<P>
Tung told Premier Li and Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji, who was on
hand, that everything has been going on "smoothly" since Hong
Kong's return over two months ago.
</P>
<P>
"Our country is very big and has been developing vary rapidly,
and it has scored great achievements, and we feel we can speak
louder internationally after the return to the motherland," Tung
said.
</P>
<P>
Li, Zhu and Hong Kong SAR ranking officials also conferred in a
relaxed, joyful and harmonious mood on the future growth of the
Hong Kong SAR and its cooperation with the interior area.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Chief Executive Tung hosted a banquet in
honor of Premier Li, Vice-Premier Zhu and their party.  
</P>
</TEXT>
