<HEADLINE> Main Computer Fails on Russia's Mir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The main computer on Russia's
Mir space station failed today, causing the gyroscopic devices on
the Mir to switch off.
</P>
<P>
A Mission Control spokeswoman said that the reasons for the
breakdown of the computer have remained unknown, local reports
said.
</P>
<P>
Mir's main computer has failed several times in recent months
and it had been fixed by the crew aboard the Mir since the crashes
on September 8 and 14.
</P>
<P>
The Mir space station, which was established in 1986, has
suffered from a series of problems recently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
