<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Announce New Industrial Policy Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is likely to
announce soon a new industrial policy which mainly targets
increase in the production and ultimately leading to export
surplus, a local newspaper reported here today.
</P>
<P>
"The major thrust of the government in the policy will be to
boost exports," the Frontier Post quoted official sources as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Carrying incentives both for increased investment and
production, the policy will not only re-activate the already
established industrial zones, but will also introduce new such
zones, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
"Establishment of a number of Pioneer Industrial Zones is on
the agenda of the government," said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the Pioneer Industrial Zones would offer
incentive packages on the pattern of the already existing zones.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the new zones will allow trading activity as a hub
of ware housing of imported produce and their re-export in freely
and convertible foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, the new industrial policy will be
followed by a package to lure domestic and foreign direct
investment. 
