<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Boost Rubber Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam will boost its rubber
industry, one of the country's major foreign currency earners, by
expanding overseas markets and making quality products, local
press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Revenues from rubber exports in 1996 amounted to 150 million
U.S. dollars, up 25 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Rubber plantations in Vietnam covered more than 260,000
hectares with an output of 160,000 tons last year, ranking fourth
in Southeast Asia after Thailand, Indonesia and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The General Rubber Company, Vietnam's biggest rubber producer,
is to export most of its 140,000 tons of items world-wide this
year.
</P>
<P>
With rubber output rising at an average of 20,000 tons each
year, the area of rubber farms is expected to be expanded to
500,000 to 700,000 hectares by the year 2005.
</P>
<P>
Of the agro-forestry export products of Vietnam, rubber ranks
third after rice and coffee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
