<HEADLINE> Italian President Calls for Unity to Face Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Scalfaro
today called on the Italians to work together to confront the
challenges facing the country.
</P>
<P>
"Our country needs everyone, at all level," said Scalfaro in
Verona, a city in northern Italy, urging cooperation along "the
difficult road" that Italy faces toward joining the single
currency, solving the unemployment crisis and realizing
constitutional reforms.
</P>
<P>
"Italy has no need for enmity," he added.
</P>
<P>
As Scalfaro spoke, some 200 protesters of the separatist
Northern League confronted the riot police, advocating the
secession of northern Italy.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the efforts to solve the unemployment crisis and
reform the welfare state, Scalfaro said, "it is not easy to come
up with a concept of the welfare state until the maximum effort
has been made at all levels to erase this plague."
</P>
<P>
The work of parliament and the governments of different
levels was instrumental in this effort, said the president.
</P>
<P>
Scalfaro traveled to Verona for ceremonies commemorating an
Italian unit massacred by the Nazis in Cophalonia. He also urged
Italians to find inspiration in those who fought for freedom and
democracy to find "a new impulse, a new enthusiasm" to work
together for the common good. 
</P>
</TEXT>
