<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Lags Behind in Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Italy is the world's fifth
industrial power but only 10th in terms of direct foreign
investment, said a world investment report from the United Nations
Conference on Trade and Development (UNCTAD), released today.
</P>
<P>
The report reported a 10 percent rise in foreign investment
last year spurred by the accelerating globalization of world
markets.
</P>
<P>
Presenting the report here, UNCTAD's Gilberto Bonalumi, who is
director of the institute for relations between Italy, Africa,
Latin America and the Middle East, said Italy risked lagging even
further behind.
</P>
<P>
"We are the world's fifth biggest exporter but only 10th in
terms of foreign investment, a long way behind Canada," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It appears rather clear that if we Italians do not understand
that we have to start working more and more with foreign countries
rather that just for foreign markets, we risk being cut out of the
globalization process; and the report shows that this process is
very fast." 
</P>
</TEXT>
