<HEADLINE> Auto Supply Expected to Far Exceed Demand in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 22 (xinhua) -- Excessive numbers of foreign
auto-making joint ventures are competing for limited shares of
Vietnam's domestic market, leading to a large amount of wasted
investment capital, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, 14 such joint ventures with 31 different models have
been licensed by the Vietnamese government.
</P>
<P>
According to official estimates, Vietnam needs about 30,000
automobiles a year. However, the country imports about 20,000 cars,
mostly used, each year and this means that only 10,000 additional
automobiles are left for the joint manufacturers yearly.
</P>
<P>
By the time all 14 joint ventures are working, they will produce
about 800-1,000 cars per month for the local market. 
</P>
