<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Manufacturing Sector Production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The production of the
Philippines' manufacturing enterprises increased in July this year
as its value and volume indices both rose considerably, the
National Statistics Office said today.
</P>
<P>
On a year-on-year basis, the Value of Production Index (VPI) of
key manufacturing enterprises increased by 6.4 percent to 454.3 in
July from 427.1 in the same month last year, according to a
monthly survey released by the office.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed that on a month-on-month basis, the VPI also
rose by 4.1 percent from June's 436.3.
</P>
<P>
Electrical machinery led all sectors with an increase of 44.2
percent which contributed the biggest share of 80.4 percent to the
6.4 percent overall increase, data showed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Volume of Production Index (VoPI) of key
manufacturing enterprises was estimated at 153.2 which was a
year-on-year increase of 5.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Electrical machinery led all sectors again with an increase of
46.6 percent which contributed the biggest share of 75.9 percent
to the positive component of the annual growth.
</P>
<P>
The VoPI is derived from VPI and Producer's Price index with
1992 as the base year. The index is a measure of change in volume,
net of inflation.
</P>
<P>
On a month-on-month basis, the VoPI increased by 4.0 percent to
153.2 in July 1997 from 147.2 in June, the survey showed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
