<HEADLINE> Tamil Businessman Arrested for Aiding Rebels in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 22 (Xinhua) -- A wealthy Tamil businessman
has been arrested in connection with an abortive rebel attempt to
blow up the Ratmalana Airport in the suburb of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The businessman is alleged to have financed the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) operations in Colombo, police sources
disclosed here today.
</P>
<P>
He had disappeared after police arrested two rebel activists
who were on a spying mission near the Ratmalana Airport. The
airport is being used as an airforce base.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan police were able to catch him at Vavuniya, in the
North province on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The businessman had assumed the Sinhala name of Kobbekaduwa and
had been responsible for distributing cash to rebels hiding in
Colombo, police said.
</P>
<P>
While carrying out a fish transport business he had also
carried messages from rebel leaders in the North and East to
terrorists infiltrated into Colombo for specific missions.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan police discovered a large arms cache of the Tamil
rebels on Tuesday night at Ratmalana, a small town some 20
kilometers south of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The rebels had planned to use explosives, hand grenades and
other weapons in the arms cache to launch a suicide attack at the
Ratmalana Airport.
</P>
<P>
Other important government facilities were also targeted by the
rebels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
