<HEADLINE> Sichuan Province of China Attracts Foreign Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province approved 105 foreign-funded projects valued at
164 million US dollars during the first half of this year, a
year-on-year rise approaching 100 percent.
</P>
<P>
Basic industry and infrastructure projects were the focus of
investments during the period, and an ever increasing number of
multinational corporations and groups have established operations
in the province.
</P>
<P>
Leshan-Phoenix Semiconductor Co. Ltd, a Sino-US joint venture
which already ranked as China's major producer of semiconductors,
invested an additional 150 million US dollars to expand its
production capacity.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong-based Henderson Properties Co. Ltd. provided funding
for the largest thermal power plant in southwest China which was
built at a cost of 2.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Sichuan recorded 1.1 billion US dollars of imports
and exports in the period, including exports of 770 million US
dollars. Foreign-funded enterprises contributed exports of 108
million US dollars, a dramatic 223.8 percent rise on
the pervious year's period. 
</P>
