<P>
The conditions that Thailand accepted in return for a 17
billion U.S. dollar international bailout were a national
commitment that would transcend the passing of governments,
Thanong said on Sunday in Hong Kong where he was attending an
IMF-world bank meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Thai minister expressed confidence that all the political
problems in Thailand will pass away by the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
The Thai parliament is scheduled to open a censure debate on
Wednesday, which was launched by the opposition in a bid to
impeach Thai Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh.
</P>
<P>
A parliamentary vote will be held following the two-day
no-confidence debate, which will be a key political event in the
country this month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
