<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Economy Becoming Increasingly Open: Vice-Premier Zhu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 22 (Xinhua) -- China's economy has become
increasingly open and it is still expanding its opening-up program
faster and more extensively, Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji said
here today.
</P>
<P>
"In today's China, the policy of reform and opening-up has been
deeply rooted in the hearts of the people and is irreversible,"
Zhu said in English at the 56th Meeting of the Development
Committee of the World Bank/International Monetary Fund in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, who arrived in Hong Kong Sunday, said the reform and
opening-up have not only brought about a much stronger economy in
China, but also helped the country integrate itself gradually with
the world economy.
</P>
<P>
In the past 19 years, China's economy has all along maintained
a momentum of rapid growth with an average annual GNP growth rate
of 9.8 percent, he said. The planned target to quadruple the GNP
of 1980 by the year 2000 was achieved in 1995 ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to China's strenuous efforts, the poverty-stricken
population in the country was reduced from 250 million to about 50
million, he said, adding that the Chinese government is fully
confident about and capable of wiping out absolute poverty by the
end of this century.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, China's total foreign trade volume reached 290 billion
U.S. dollars, over 36 percent of the year's GNP, ranking 11th in
the world against the 32nd in 1978 when China began its reform and
opening-up program.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China's trade volume will be further expanded to
400 billion U.S. dollars by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, with the improvement of China's investment
environment, a total of over 280 billion US dollars of external
capital has been actually used in China, of which over 170 billion
dollars are foreign direct investment.
</P>
<P>
China has been the largest foreign capital recipient among the
developing countries over the past three years, Zhu said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
