<HEADLINE> China's 1st Private Bank To Improve Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The Minsheng Bank
Corporation, the first non-government banking institution in
China, has decided to use more democratic and scientific methods
in future.
</P>
<P>
Bank executives will be limited in power and an examination and
supervision system will be set up in major departments, according
to Cai Lulun, who recently replaced Dong Yinzeng as president.
</P>
<P>
It was founded early last year, as a result of the country's
reform and opening-up drive and the rapidly developing private
economy, as a stock-issuing commercial bank with 85 percent of its
capital coming from private companies, Cai told Xinhua in a recent
interview. Its main clients are private businesses, which are a
rapidly-growing part of the national economy.
</P>
<P>
Minsheng now has 12 billion yuan in assets, according to
Cai. "The capital is small, but the key is the quality," he noted.
</P>
<P>
As a new bank, it needs to give priority to its share-holders,
he added, and should safeguard their interests, while they in turn
should act in accordance with the commercial bank law. 
</P>
