<HEADLINE> CPC Congress Has Impacts on World, Says Bulgarian Writer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Writers' Association
Chairman Nikolai Khaitov said today that the decisions adopted
by the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) are "of world significance."
</P>
<P>
Khaitov, 78, who has been following the developments of the
socialist cause in China, said that China led by its outstanding
leader Deng Xiaoping has made great progress during the last two
decades.
</P>
<P>
One of the most important decisions of the CPC congress is to
put Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics into the party constitution as "a guiding
thought." It will not only guide the way for China's economic
modernization but also for its cultural advance, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Now that we have come to know the answer to 'what is socialism
and how to build socialism,' there are new prospects to spread
socialism in political practices in the whole world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Khaitov, who had a deep impression on the report given by
General Secretary of the CPC Central Committee Jiang Zemin at the
congress, said he really appreciated China's idea to build a world
of multi-polarization.
</P>
<P>
He believed that China's creative experience in politics and
economic development will reduce the differences between countries
of different sizes, strength and wealth, saying that this is the
biggest comfort that the CPC congress resolutions have offered to
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
