<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cotton Purchasing Policy Effective </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese cotton growers are
actively selling their products to the State thanks to stable
purchase policies, China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
The All China Federation of Supply and Marketing Cooperatives,
which is in charge of the country's cotton purchase work, said a
federation official that as of last Monday, the State had
purchased about 3 million kilograms of new cotton. The majority
from Xinjiang, Hubei, Henan, Sichuan and Jiangsu, the country's
leading cotton producers.
</P>
<P>
Northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, the
nation's top cotton-producing region, is expected to harvest a
total of 11.5 million kilograms of cotton this year, all of which
will be bought by the state, according to the federation.
</P>
<P>
The federation has issued a set of rules to standardize cotton
purchase, safeguard the interests of cotton growers and ensure the
quality of the cotton purchased.
</P>
<P>
Under the rules, cotton purchasing stations and processing
factories are under the direct leadership of county and city-level
cotton and linen companies and they must obtain permits from
companies at provincial or regional level before they begin cotton
purchases.
</P>
<P>
The main tasks of cotton purchasing units include
implementation of official policies and purchase standards,
fulfilment of purchasing quotas on time and with good quality, and
promotion of a new scientific approach, new skills and fine new
cotton seeds.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
