<HEADLINE> Chechen Republic President Meets Delegations From Britain, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Aslan Maskhadov, president of
the Chenchen Republic, met delegations from Britain and Germany
Sunday to arrange the founding of a London-based Caucasian Fund,
said a report reaching here from Grozny, Chechnya's capital.
</P>
<P>
The British delegation, whose country will participate as
co-founders in the Caucasian Fund, told Maskhadov that they lack
information about the state of affairs in Chechnya coming on a
permanent basis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of kidnaps in Chechnya, Lord Alister McAlrain, a
member of the House of Lords, also a member of the British
delegation, said this problem exists throughout the world. No
country has the right to give advice to Chechens on how to settle
it until it settles this problem on its own territory, he added.
</P>
<P>
The German delegation said they need to have more information
about Chechnya and that they wish to develop friendly relations
between the two sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
