<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Mobile Communications Network Improved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- A public "130" digital mobile
communication network with a handling capacity of 15,000 lines has
opened in Nanning, capital of south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The new network supplements the handling capacity of the local
current "138" and "139" public digital mobile communication
networks operated by China Telecom.
</P>
<P>
The new network was opened by the China United
Telecommunications Corp. (Unicom), a large state-owned company
authorized by the Chinese government to provide basic telecom
services. Unicom has opened "130" digital networks in 28 domestic
cities.
</P>
<P>
The region is currently home to more than 230,000 mobile phone
subscribers, with one in every 200 people currently owning a
mobile phone.
</P>
<P>
The region's post and telecommunications sector recorded a
total business turnover of 1.68 billion yuan in the first half of
this year alone, up 37 percent on the same 1996 period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
