<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Packaging Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 22 (Xinhua) -- China's packaging industry
is expected to generate an output value of 220 billion yuan by the
year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The industry's current fixed assets of 72 billion yuan
now form an independent and relatively complete industrial
system. Five sectors -- papermaking, plastics, glass, metal and
printing -- have introduced advanced technology and equipment in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
The sector's output value hit 126 billion yuan in l996, up 10
percent on 1995.
</P>
<P>
The industry has witnessed a rapid growth since 1990, with its
annual output value between 1990-1995 surging by 152.2 percent to
114.5 billion yuan, an annual average of 20.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
