<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats New Zealand 5-0 in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazil continued its winning
streak over New Zealand by sweeping two matches in four sets in
Davis Cup competition Sunday in Florianopolis, Brazil.
</P>
<P>
In the first match, it took Brazil's Gustavo Kuerten, 11th in
ATP world ranking, just 50 minutes to beat New Zealand's Bret
Steven 6-1, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
Andre Sa, No. 198, then beat 209th ranked Alistair Hunt 6-2, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, Brazil routed New Zealand 3-0 in doubles play to
return it to the Davis Cup's World Group. 
