<HEADLINE> Brazil, Venezuela Wins Men's World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazil beat Argentina
3-2 to secure a first place division finish in a men's volleyball
World Cup qualifier match on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Brazil won 15-4, 14-16, 15-3, 9-15 and 15-10 before a partisan
crowd at Rio's Miecimo da Silva Sports Center.
</P>
<P>
In another match of the day, it took Venezuela only 42 minutes
to down Peru 15-2, 15-4 and 15-3.
</P>
<P>
Brazil won its South American qualifying division followed by
Argentina, Venezuela and Peru. Only the two top teams will gain
berth in next year's World Cup games in Japan. 
