<DOCNO> XIE19970922.0223 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China County Develops Largest Almond Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 22 (Xinhua) -- Pingquan county, north
China's Hebei Province, has developed an almond market with an
annual transaction volume of 20 million tons, the largest of the
kind in the northern part of the country.
</P>
<P>
Traders on the market come from many northern Chinese provinces,
including the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, Liaoning, and
Shaanxi. They contribute an annual transaction volume of 100
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
At present, Pingquan has 30,000 ha of apricots, with a total
output of one million tons annually.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the county placed emphasis on almond processing
industry. It has ten almond processing enterprises and 13 active
carbon plants, with the annual output value of almond syrup,
almond powder and pit carbon totaling 80 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
