<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Beats Austria for a Berth in World Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe joined the World
Group of tennis nations Sunday after defeating a Thomas Muster-led
Austria 3-2 in their Davis Cup qualifying round.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for the southern African nation to qualify
for the World Group since their first competing in the Davis Cup
34 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Victory was assured in the final reverse singles when Wayne
Black, lagging from behind, outplayed Gerald Mandl 6-3, 6-3, 6-0.
Mandl replaced Austrian number two, Gilbert Schaller, who had
stomach cramps.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Austrian, playing only his third Davis Cup
match, became unsettled after several foot faults.
</P>
<P>
In the other reverse singles, Muster was shocked by Byron
Black, finding himself down 1-2. But his greater power and
improving cross-court play finally beat his opponent 3-6, 6-3,
2-6, 6-3, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
In the round's previous matches, Muster beat Wayne Black, Byron
Black beat Schaller and the Blacks beat Mandl and Georg Blumayor
in the doubles. All those matches were concluded in straight
sets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970922.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwestern People Benefit From Water Tapping Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- China's water-tapping program
in its arid northwestern area has located a number of significant
underground water sources this year, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
A newly discovered underground water source in Tongxin county
of the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region provides the local
inhabitants with 30,000 cubic meters of water each day, according
to the Ministry of Geology and Mineral Resources.
</P>
<P>
Another high yield well, which was drilled by geological teams
in Fuping county of northern Shaanxi Province, can produce 13,300
cubic meters of potable mineral water a year.
</P>
<P>
The ministry earmarked 18 million yuan (2.1 million US dollars)
to tap the area's underground water this year.
</P>
<P>
To help tap 10 such projects, the State Planning Commission has
approved providing another 20 million yuan (2.4 million US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The money was taken from the compensation fees collected from
the country's mining units to be spent on the protection of the
country's mineral resources.
</P>
<P>
Other new discoveries include five underground water locations
with a daily water supply of 3,000 cubic meters in Qinghai
province.
</P>
<P>
That is enough water to irrigate 13 hectares of vegetables and
66 hectares of grain, while at the same time meeting the water
needs of the 2,400 local inhabitants.
</P>
<P>
In the midst of the drive to tap new water sources, the
geological teams also are concerned with the development of
already discovered water supplies.
</P>
<P>
A geological team discovered three underground water sources in
xinjiang and set up a shareholding farm with the Agricultural
College of the region.
</P>
<P>
Under their joint management, the farm has planted 66 hectares
of crops with an estimated annual output value of 300,000 yuan
(36,000 US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
