<HEADLINE> Russia's Pavel Tonkov Wins 15th Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Pavel Tonkov won the
15th stage of the Tour of Spain Sunday as Spain's Fernando
Escartin moved into the overall No. 2 position.
</P>
<P>
Tonkov, who also grabbed the Tour's 13th stage, overtook
Escartin three kilometers from the finish to win with a time of
four hours three minutes and 55 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's race was a 159-kilometer ride from the northern city
of Oviedo to the Covadonga Lakes in Cangas de Onis.
</P>
<P>
The Russian had said he planned to quit the race to go see his
newborn son, Nicholas, in Madrid after winning Friday's stage, but
changed his mind when the Tour planners flew him in for a
few-hours visit.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland's Alex Zulle pulled out way ahead in the overall
standings. With a time of 64 hours, 57 minutes, 55 seconds, he is
2:46 ahead of the pack.
</P>
<P>
Monday's stage is a 195-kilometer race from Cangas de Onis to
the Atlantic coastal city of Santander. 
</P>
</TEXT>
