<HEADLINE> China To Issue Silver Tourism Year Coins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China
(PBOC) will issue a silver commemorative coin in late September,
to mark the 1997 China Tourism Year.
</P>
<P>
Liu Xiaojun, head of the secretariat of 97' China Tourism
Year's organizing committee, said it will be China's first
commemorative coin on tourism.
</P>
<P>
He said that one side shows the Temple of Heaven in Beijing and
has the characters for "97'China Tourism Year", and the other side
shows a giant panda.
</P>
<P>
A total of 50,000 coins made from an ounce of pure silver each
will be sold. The coin is 40 millimeters in diameter and has a
face value of 10 yuan (about 1.2 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Zhu Chunde, deputy manager of the China Gold Coin Corp., says
the silvers coins, which are to be made by his company, will be
available at National Tourism Administration shops and will also
be sold overseas.  
</P>
