<HEADLINE> Swedes to Clash Americans in Davis Cup World Group Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The Swedish tennis team
will clash with the United States team in this year's world group
final of the Davis Cup tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Sweden reached the final for the second straight year by
winning over Italy 4-1 in Norrkoeping on Sunday, while the United
States defeating Australia 4-1 in Washington.
</P>
<P>
The Swedes advanced when Jonas Bjorkman downed Renzo Furlan
4-6, 6-4, 6-0, 6-4 in the reverse singles to take 3-1 winning lead
over Italy.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Enqvist then made it 4-1 with a 6-3, 6-7 (5-7), 6-3 win
over Omar Camporese as the Swedes advanced to the final for the
11th time since 1975.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman won all three of his matches over the weekend to be
the key to the Swedish win.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the French team defeated the Swedish team 3-2 in the
final.
</P>
<P>
This time the Swedes will host the Americans from November
28-30 as they seek their sixth title.
</P>
<P>
The United States have won the Cup in 1990, 1992 and 1995,
while Sweden last triumphed in 1994.
</P>
<P>
It will be the 59th Davis Cup final for the US team, which has
won a record 31 titles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
