<HEADLINE> United States Beats Australia 4-1 in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 21 (Xinhua) -- World number one Pete
Sampras downed U.S. Open champion Patrick Rafter on Sunday and
lead the United States into the Davis Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, playing at the absolute top of his form, powered his
way past the third-ranked Rafter 6-7 (6-8), 6-1, 6-1, 6-4 to give
the United States an anbeatable 3-1 lead over Australia in the
best-of-five World Group semifinals.
</P>
