<HEADLINE> Brazil Wins Under-17 Soccer World Cup Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazil grabbed the Under-17
World Cup crown by beating defending champion Ghana 2-1 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier match for third place, Spain defeated Germany 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, which went all out for the revenge of the 2-3 defeat by
Ghana in the finals of the last U-17 World Cup in Ecuador in 1995,
played a tough game Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Afriye Owusu put Ghana ahead in the 39th minute with a left
shot and his squad ratained the edge at halftime.
</P>
<P>
Brazil equalized in the 64th when the Ghanaian goalie, Boateng
Osei, failed to hold a full-blooded kick by Ronaldo Moreira.
Matuzalem Silva took the rebouding ball and slammed it into the
net.
</P>
<P>
Just three minutes before the final whistle, Andrey Moreira
gained the victory for the South American team with a winning goal
after he took a superb pass from near the penalty area.
</P>
<P>
Ghana paid for missing several chances, including 10 corners
compared to three that Brazil took and failed to score. 
</P>
</TEXT>
