<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Output on Quick Growth in January-July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 22 (Xinhua) -- China generated 3.96 trillion
yuan in industrial output during the first seven months this year,
up 13.1 percent over the same period in 1996, according to the
latest statistics from State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The output of light industry stood at 1.75 trillion yuan-worth,
up 13.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of heavy industry was 2.2 trillion yuan-worth, up 12.5
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
