<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dutch, Belgian Telecom Companies Join in Soccer Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Dutch PTT Telecom and
Belgian telephone company Belgacom are joining forces in a bid for
communication services at the 2000 European soccer championship,
it was learned here today.
</P>
<P>
Together they want to be responsible for the full installation
of the international press centers and facilities for all TV,
radio, telephone and fax links needed for reporting the event.
</P>
<P>
News media such as Internet are expected to play a prominent
role at the games, according to sources close to the European
Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
