<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Wins Five Titles at World Sports Acrobatics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANCHESTER, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The four-day 1997 World
Sports Abrobatics Championships ended at Manchester's National
Cycling Center this evening, with China winning five of the 21
world titles.
</P>
<P>
At the all-around final of the men's pairs competition, China's
world champions Song Min and Li Renjie, who collected two
individual mens pairs titles, successfully defended their
all-around honor. Although Russia's pair competitors tried every
means to upset the Chinese duo, the almost perfect Chinese
performance sent Russia's gold dreams crashing.
</P>
<P>
After winning their first women's pairs balance title, China's
new pair combination Lao Peiling/Liao Xinxin snatched their
all-around gold medals by convincingly beating their Ukrainian
arch-rivals with a 10-point score.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Chinese team also won another bonze medals in
the finals of men's tumbling, men's groups and women's groups
events.
</P>
<P>
The world sports acrobatics powerhouses Russia and Ukraine won
12 and 5 titles respectively. Meanwhile, highly encouraged by
strong home crowds, the British team certainly became the darkest
horse of the championships by pocketing two gold and two silver
medals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
