<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Endorses Directive on Comparative Advertising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 21 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)
Council of Ministers and the European Parliament have approved a
directive on comparative advertising over which they had long been
divided, it was learned here today.
</P>
<P>
This endorses the compromise reached in June by a conciliation
committee and draws to a close almost five years of intense
inter-institutional discussions.
</P>
<P>
The new legislation, which the EU member states will be
required to transpose within 30 months of its imminent entry into
force, amends related EU directive on misleading advertising to
include comparative advertising.
</P>
<P>
Comparative advertising is defined as advertising referring
to a competitor or to goods or services offered by a competitor.
</P>
<P>
According to the Directive text, comparative advertising can be
authorized provided that it neither gives rise to market confusion
nor discredits or denigrates a competitor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
