<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Killed in California Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 21 (Xinhua) -- Authorities in Southern
California of the United states said Sunday a small airplane
crashed into a medical building in Torrance, killing at least one
person and touching off a major fire.
</P>
<P>
No one on the ground was injured.
</P>
<P>
It's not immediately clear how many people were aboard the
single-engine Beechcraft Sundowner, but the United Press
International quoted Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) as
saying "there are no apparent survivors."
</P>
<P>
Authorities in Torrance have confirmed at least one person
aboard the plane is dead, and it's possible two others also have
died.
</P>
<P>
The Torrance Fire Department said the blaze in the three-story
building was extinguished with the help of fire-fighters from the
nearby cities of Redondo Beach and Gardena as well as some from
the Los Angeles County Fire Department.
</P>
<P>
The National Transportation Safety Board is on scene to
investigate the cause of the crash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
